instructionText:
In this experiment, you will be listening to sentences and rating the naturalness of the speech.

First, you will hear a recording of a full sentence. After the sentence is played, you will see a rating scale. Your task is to rate how natural the speaker's pronunciation sounded on a scale from 1 (very unnatural) to 7 (very natural).

When you are ready to begin, press SPACE to continue.
instructionTextwithPractice:
In this experiment, you will be listening to sentences and rating the naturalness of the sentences.

First, you will hear a recording of a full sentence. After the sentence is played, you will see a rating scale. Your task is to rate how natural the speaker's pronunciation sounded on a scale from 1 (extremely unnatural) to 7 (extremely natural).

Press SPACE to continue.

First, we will begin with a few practice trials.

You can use these trials to test and adjust your volume appropriately.

When you're ready, press SPACE to begin.
keyChoiceText:
Press '1' for same.

Press '0' for different.
sliderPromptText: On a scale from 1 (very unnatural) to 7 (very natural), how natural does the speech sound?
breakMessage:
Feel free to take a break!

When you're ready to continue, press SPACE to begin the next trial.
